|si scocca~: Literally, "is shot forth," as an arrow
from a bowstring.  The tone of the expression adds to the note of
challenge; it means, freely, "what I now let fly."  See ^Purg.~
XXV, 17-18: "Scocca / l'arco del dir."
..TCHR:
